    ", s n (n)) as the score sequence of the tournament.",
    "Tournaments provide a model for a statistical inference called paired comparisons.",
    "Measuring players' strength in chess tournaments by modeling paired comparisons of strength has a long history, first appearing in Zermelo (1929).",
    "An excellent introduction to the combinatorial and some probabilistic aspects (with citations to earlier works) is given in Moon (1968).",
    "The statistical aspects are presented in David (1988) (also with citations to earlier works)."
